# Sales OS Code Owners
#
# This file defines who owns and is responsible for reviewing changes to different
# parts of the codebase. Owners are automatically requested for review when PRs
# affect their owned files.
#
# Format: path pattern @owner1 @owner2
# Use * for wildcards, ** for recursive matching
# Order matters - more specific patterns should come first

# Global owners - required for all changes
* @sales-os/engineering-lead @sales-os/tech-lead

# Governance and documentation - requires technical leadership approval
.cursor/rules/** @sales-os/tech-lead @sales-os/engineering-manager
docs/** @sales-os/tech-lead @sales-os/tech-writer
memory/** @sales-os/tech-lead @sales-os/engineering-manager

# Architecture decisions - requires architecture review
docs/DECISIONS/** @sales-os/tech-lead @sales-os/architect

# Security-critical files - requires security team review
# Add patterns for security-related code when implemented
# src/**/auth/** @sales-os/security-team
# src/**/security/** @sales-os/security-team

# Frontend code - requires frontend team review
# src/frontend/** @sales-os/frontend-team
# src/web/** @sales-os/frontend-team

# Backend/API code - requires backend team review
# src/backend/** @sales-os/backend-team
# src/api/** @sales-os/backend-team

# Data layer - requires data team review
# src/data/** @sales-os/data-team
# src/database/** @sales-os/data-team

# Infrastructure and DevOps - requires DevOps team review
# infrastructure/** @sales-os/devops-team
# deployment/** @sales-os/devops-team
# .github/workflows/** @sales-os/devops-team

# Testing code - requires QA team review
# tests/** @sales-os/qa-team
# src/**/test/** @sales-os/qa-team

# Configuration files - requires DevOps and security review
# config/** @sales-os/devops-team @sales-os/security-team
# .env* @sales-os/devops-team @sales-os/security-team

# Package and dependency files - requires security review
# package.json @sales-os/security-team
# requirements.txt @sales-os/security-team
# go.mod @sales-os/security-team
# Cargo.toml @sales-os/security-team

# CI/CD configuration - requires DevOps and security review
.github/** @sales-os/devops-team @sales-os/security-team

# Documentation files - technical writer owns, tech lead reviews
*.md @sales-os/tech-writer @sales-os/tech-lead
docs/*.md @sales-os/tech-writer @sales-os/tech-lead

# Special files requiring multiple approvals
# Critical infrastructure changes
# docker-compose.yml @sales-os/devops-team @sales-os/tech-lead @sales-os/security-team
# Dockerfile* @sales-os/devops-team @sales-os/security-team

# Emergency contacts (for when teams are not available)
# If no specific owners are available, these will be contacted:
# * @sales-os/emergency-contact-1 @sales-os/emergency-contact-2

# Instructions for maintainers:
# 1. Keep this file up to date as team structure changes
# 2. Add specific patterns before general ones
# 3. Use team names that match your GitHub team structure
# 4. Consider backup owners for critical paths
# 5. Review and update quarterly during team restructuring

# Current team placeholders (replace with actual team names):
# @sales-os/engineering-lead - Engineering leadership
# @sales-os/tech-lead - Technical leadership
# @sales-os/engineering-manager - Engineering management
# @sales-os/tech-writer - Technical writing team
# @sales-os/architect - Architecture team
# @sales-os/security-team - Security team
# @sales-os/frontend-team - Frontend development team
# @sales-os/backend-team - Backend development team
# @sales-os/data-team - Data engineering team
# @sales-os/devops-team - DevOps/Infrastructure team
# @sales-os/qa-team - Quality assurance team
